    <p> Clicking on the `Check Truth Table Now!' button will do just
    that, i.e., it will check to see that you have filled in the truth
    table correctly.  If you have not, you should get a helpful
    response telling you what went wrong, and a copy of your truth
    table in a new box in which you can make the necessary
    corrections.</p>

<h3>Determining Validity</h3>

    <p> Once your truth table is correct, you will be presented with a
    page that asks you to assess its validity.  The relevant portion
    of the page looks like this:</p>

	  <center>
	  <FORM>
	    <table border=3 width=90%>
	      <tr>
		<td>
		  <table border=0>
		    <tr>
		      <td>&nbsp;</td>
		      <td>
			<tt>A B | (~A -> (~B -> A))&nbsp;&nbsp;B :. ~~A</tt>
		      </td>
		      <tr>
			<td>&nbsp;</td>
			<td>
			  <tt>----|----------------------------</tt>
			</td>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			<td>
			  <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="row_0" VALUE="checked">
			</td>
			<td><pre>T T |  F  T   F  T       T    TF </td></pre>
		      </tr>	
		      <tr>
			<td>
			  <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="row_1" VALUE="checked">
			</td>
			<td><pre>T F |  F  T   T  T       F    TF </td></pre>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			<td>
			  <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="row_2" VALUE="checked">
			</td>
			<td><pre>F T |  T  T   F  T       T    FT </td></pre>
		      </tr>
		      <tr>
			<td>
			  <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="row_3" VALUE="checked">
			</td>
